data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** The syntax is straightforward:

```csharp
Span<nint>  span  = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> uspan = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

This works in safe code — no `unsafe` needed for the allocation itself. On this 64-bit system, each element is 8 bytes. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` still requires an `unsafe` context (or you can use `nint.Size` / `IntPtr.Size` instead).
